## GraphQL API

### Getting Auth Tokens

You can use `ApiToken.issue!(user:, name:)` to get a bearer auth token in Rails. There's also a binstub to pipe auth tokens directly into your GraphQL queries:

```bash
cd /path/to/your/repo
bin/api-token api@superstack.dev
```

### Making Queries

```bash
cd /path/to/your/repo

curl -s -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -X POST http://localhost:3000/graphql \
  -d '{"query":"{ health { status } }"}'

bin/api-token | xargs -I% curl -s -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'Authorization: %' -X POST http://localhost:3000/graphql \
  -d '{"query":"{ users { id email role } }"}'
```

## Stripe Billing

Use the `--with-stripe` argument when starting your development server to listen for Stripe webhooks:

```bash
cd /path/to/your/repo
bin/dev --with-stripe
```

### Set Stripe API Keys

```yaml
# config/application.yml

# replace with your Stripe test keys
# https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys

stripe_secret_key:      sk_test_REPLACE_ME
stripe_publishable_key: pk_test_REPLACE_ME
stripe_signing_secret:  whsec_REPLACE_ME
```

Obtain `stripe_signing_secret` by running `bin/dev --with-stripe`. You'll see terminal output like the following:

```bash
22:58:43 stripe.1    | Ready! You are using Stripe API Version [2017-12-14]. Your webhook signing secret is whsec_REPLACE_ME (^C to quit)
```

### Subscriptions

```yaml
# config/application.yml

# replace with your Stripe price ids
stripe_price_pro_monthly:  price_REPLACE_ME
stripe_price_pro_yearly:   price_REPLACE_ME
```

Update `price_monthly_cents` and `price_yearly_cents` in `app/models/billing/pro_plan.rb` to your product prices.
